captions.text:
Dani, Gustavo and Elidio will play.
Stand up.

When I say 'change', they must
change the last thing
I'd like the last person in the last row...
Right. I'd like you to give me a syllable.

And I'd like the person
who is on the extreme left
to give me the rest of the word: Cu...

'cause my brother can't
read what I wrote!

- Oh, I think I will take a shower.
- Change!

- Oh, I think I'll take a glass of juice.
- Change!
Oh, I think I'll shave myself.

- My daughter, are you there?
- Change!

- My wife, is anyone here?
- Change!

- I'm just here to give you some money...
- Change!

- I'm just here to make love to you...
- Change!

I'm just here because 'estoy'
about to die, I have cancer!

- 'Dear diary, yesterday I went to a party
and everybody was there'. - Change!

- 'Dear diary, I went to a hip-hop
club yesterday'. - Change!
'Dear diary, you're not that dear to me'.

- I can't believe you're
reading my diary! - Change!

Go die somewhere else!
My bedroom is mine alone!

- Oh, the house is mine!
- Change!
We live out in the streets!
If I live out in the streets, dad...

- It's because you couldn't
buy me a bedroom! - Change!

- You couldn't buy me a bathroom!
- Change!
You couldn't buy me a decent shaving!

Because if I had a good shave,
I could get a hell of a house!

'Shave yourself, monkey Cheeta'!
Anderson Bizzocchi's pure charm!
